ZetboxBase:DateTimeProperty.ZetboxBase:Description: License is valid thru
ZetboxBase:DateTimeProperty.ZetboxBase:HelpText:
Do not set values larger than 1.1.2038 (or set only even smaller values)

Postgres on Linux (not all!) will be confused about the convertion and may result in a date with 1 or 2 hours offset. Thus not the same date as saved and signed.

Possible solutions

  • Find out more about timezones in Linux
  • Store 3 Ints (day, month, year)
  • Try an explicit date data type in database (be aware! this should be optional, as the impact of other date only values is unpredictable)
